Let's return to some of the layouts
we looked at in lesson one and

24
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:13,670
see how they might
work on larger devices.

25
00:01:13,670 --> 00:01:16,910
Now, as the screen width
increases with this layout

26
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:20,760
The line length the text increases
is making harder to read.

27
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:23,480
So, you might want to have
a break point somewhere

28
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:27,230
where the line length exceeds
45 to 75 character guideline.

29
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:29,720
In this form layout,

30
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:34,470
on wider devices there's too much
unused space, here on the right.

31
00:01:34,470 --> 00:01:36,500
Making it feel unbalanced.

32
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:42,490
You might set a break point round about
say here to re balance the layout.

33
